"post-truth" is a term coined by the British political scientist Matthew Goodwin in a study published in April 2016. It refers to the phenomenon of politicians, journalists and other public figures misleading or lying to the public in order to further their own political aims.

"Post-truth" is a neologism that was created to describe the phenomenon of the spread of false information on social media. It was coined by the editors-in-chief of the Oxford Dictionary of English, published in September 2016.

